                                        <p>Figure 6 shows how real housing costs for renters and owners since 2007. Total mortgage payments have increased slower than the rent payments. The principal payments have increased more significantly than rents. his is driven by increased house prices. The mortgage interest rates have decreased as a result of progressively lower interest rates. <strong>The higher increase in cost of renting compared to homeownership has potentially led to increased demand and higher HPG over the last decade</strong>.</p>
